---
description: Enforce Chinese-English bilingual support for frontend and backend
alwaysApply: true
---

# Bilingual Support (zh-CN / en-US)

- All user-facing text must support both Chinese and English.
- Frontend:
  - Do not hardcode UI text in components; use i18n keys.
  - New pages and features must provide both `zh-cn` and `en-us` locale entries.
  - API requests should send `Accept-Language` (or an equivalent language header).
- Backend:
  - Do not return hardcoded single-language error messages in controller/service responses.
  - Error and prompt messages must be localized based on request language (`Accept-Language`).
  - Default language should be `zh-CN` when header is missing.
- PR checklist:
  - Added/updated i18n keys in both languages.
  - Verified one zh flow and one en flow for affected endpoints/pages.
